    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Calycohyllum candidissimum, native to Cuba, Mexico, Columbia and Venezuela. It has a non-durable heartwood ranging in color from light brown to tan, and is used for making archery bows, fishing rods, and tool handles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
